info.title: The Hymnbook
info.notes: Published in 1955 by five Presbyterian-Reformed denominations. This is a standard collection of traditional hymns with a strong emphasis on Psalter selections and Psalm paraphrases. Permission was granted to use these titles and indexes by: Robin Howell Rights Manager Westminster John Knox Press and Presbyterian Publishing Corporation 100 Witherspoon St. Louisville, KY 40202-139 502-569-5067

hymn.title: Praise ye the Lord, the Almighty, the King of creation
For the beauty of the earth
Praise the Lord: ye heavens, adore Him
Praise the Lord, His glories show
O Lord, Thou art my God and King
hymn.scripture: Acts 14:15-17; II Corinthians 10:5; Mark 7:37; Psalms 100; Psalms 145:3

hymn.title: Heaven and earth, and sea and air
Of the Father's love begotten
Bless, O my soul! the living God
Now thank we all our God
hymn.scripture: Colossians 2:7; Philippians 4:6-7; Psalms 100:4; Psalms 107:1; Psalms 107:31; Psalms 107:8

hymn.title: Mighty God, while angels bless Thee
hymn.scripture: I Chronicles 29:11; II Corinthians 9:15; I Timothy 1:16-17; Psalms 117; Psalms 136

hymn.title: Holy, Holy, Holy!. Lord God Almighty
Lord of health, Thou life within us
God Himself is with us
Lord of the worlds above
Sing praise to God who reigns above
We come unto our fathers' God
We praise Thee, o God, our Redeemer, Creator
We gather together to ask the Lord's blessing
Praise God, ye servants of the Lord
It is good to sing Thy praises
Joyful, joyful, we adore Thee
Let all the world in every corner sing
All nature's works His praise declare
All people that on earth do dwell
We worship Thee, almighty Lord
O worship the King all glorious above
Ye servants of God, your Master proclaim
Let us with a gladsome mind
O come and sing unto the Lord
Angel voices, ever singing
Praise, my soul, the King of heaven
What shall I render to the Lord
From all that dwell below the skies
Ye watchers and ye holy ones
All ye that fear God's holy name
Praise ye the Lord, for it is good
O sing a new song to the Lord
The earth, with all that dwell therein
Come, ye people, rise and sing
Open now thy gates of beauty
When morning gilds the skies
As the sun doth daily rise
Father, we praise Thee, now the night is over
Come, my soul, thou must be waking
New every morning is the love
O Splendor of God's glory bright
Christ, whose glory fills the skies
Hear my words, O gracious Lord
When morning lights the eastern skies
Awake, my soul and with the sun
Now the day is over
On the good and faithful
Now God be with us, for the night is closing
Saviour, breathe an evening blessing
At even, when the sun was set
Sun of my soul, Thou Saviour dear
Before the day draws near its ending
God, that madest earth and heaven
The day Thou gavest, Lord, is ended
Softly now the light of day
O gladsome light, O grace of God
Again, as evening's shadow falls
All praise to Thee, my God, this night
Abide with me: fast falls the eventide
Day is dying in the west
Now woods and wolds are sleeping
Now, on land and sea descending
When in the night I meditate
This is the day the Lord hath made
O day of rest and gladness
The glorious gates of righteousness
This is the day of light
Light of light, enlighten me
Safely through another week
Praise our Father for this Sunday
May the grace of Christ our Saviour
Saviour, again to Thy dear name we raise
God be with you till we meet again
Lord, dismiss us with Thy blessing
On our way rejoicing
Before Jehovah's awful throne
Thy mercy and Thy truth, O Lord
The Lord is King! lift up thy voice
I sing the mighty power of God
Immortal, invisible, God only wise
Begin, my tongue, some heavenly theme
Lord of all being, throned afar
Lord, Thou hast been our dwelling place
The God of Abraham praise
God, the Lord, a King remaineth
A mighty Fortress is our God
O God, the Rock of Ages
O God, Thou art the Father
The Lord Almighty reigns
O Lord, our Lord, in all the earth
All beautiful the march of days
The spacious firmament on high
Praise ye, praise ye the Lord 98
Thy might sets fast the mountains
All creatures of our God and King
This is my Father's world
God, who touchest earth with beauty
God is Love, His mercy brightens
The Lord's my Shepherd, I'll not want
How gentle God's commands
The King of love my Shepherd is
Father, long before creation
God of our life, through all the circling years
I bow my forehead to the dust
There's a wideness in God's mercy
O God, our Help in ages past
God moves in a mysterious way
My soul with expectation doth
I look to Thee in every need
Praise the Lord, for He is good
O Love divine, that stooped to share
By all whom Thou hast made
O Love of God most full
When all Thy mercies, O my God
Behold the amazing gift of love
O thou my soul, bless God the Lord
God of compassion, in mercy befriend us
Call Jehovah thy Salvation
Be not dismayed whate're betide
Come, let us to the Lord our God
In sweet communion, Lord, with Thee
O Lord, by Thee delivered
Our God, to whom we turn
O Lord my inmost heart and thought
How sweet the name of Jesus sounds
Come, Christians, join to sing
All hail the power of Jesus' name
Look, ye saints, the sight is glorious
O could I speak the matchless worth
Fairest Lord Jesus
Christ is the world's redeemer
Blessing and honor and glory and power
Light of the world, we hail Thee
Blessed assurance, Jesus is mine
hymn.scripture: II Corinthians 5:1; I John 3:2; I Peter 1:8

hymn.title: Rejoice, the Lord is King
O for a thousand tongues to sing
Majestic sweetness sits enthroned
hymn.scripture: I Corinthians 6:20; Psalms 46:2; Psalms 46:7; Song of Solomon 5:10; Song of Solomon 5:16

hymn.title: At the name of Jesus
I greet Thee; who my sure Redeemer art
O light, whose beams illumine all
Hail to the Lord's Anointed
O come, O come, Emmanuel
Let all mortal flesh keep silence
Watchman, tell us of the night
Hark, what a sound, and too divine for hearing
Come, Thou long-expected Jesus
Lift up your heads, ye mighty gates
The race that long in darkness pined
Silent night! holy night
There's a song in the air
The first Noel the angel did say
Away in a manger, no crib for His bed
Angels we have heard on high
What Child is this, who laid to rest
It came upon the midnight clear
Joy to the world! the Lord is come
Lo, how a rose e're blooming
hymn.scripture: Isaiah 11:1; Isaiah 11:10; Luke 2:7; Song of Solomon 2:1

hymn.title: Hark, the herald angels sing
Infant holy
Good Christian men, rejoice
God rest you merry, gentlemen
Gentle Mary laid her Child
Angels, from the realms of glory
While shepherds watched their flocks by night
O come, all ye faithful
O little town of Bethlehem
All my heart this night rejoices
Ah, dearest Jesus, holy Child
As with gladness men of old
Brightest and best of the sons of the morning
We three kings of orient are
O sing a song of Bethlehem
O Master Workman of the race
Thine arm, O Lord, in days of old
What grace, O Lord, and beauty shone
Lord, who throughout these forty days
O wondrous type, O vision fair
We would see Jesus; lo! His star is shining
Thou didst leave Thy throne and Thy kingly crown
Hosanna, loud hosanna
When, His salvation bringing
All glory, laud, and honor
Ride on! ride on in majesty
'Tis midnight; and on olive's brow
Beneath the cross of Jesus
Ah, holy Jesus, how hast Thou offended
O come and mourn with me awhile
Go to dark Gethsemane
O sacred Head, now wounded
In the cross of Christ I glory
Cross of Jesus, cross of sorrow
Throned upon the awful tree
When I survey the wondrous cross
Alas! and did my Saviour bleed
O Jesus, we adore Thee
Were you there when they crucified my Lord
There is a green hill far away
The strife is o'er, the battle done
hymn.scripture: I Corinthians 15:20; I Corinthians 15:57; II Timothy 1:10

hymn.title: Jesus Christ is risen today
hymn.scripture: I Corinthians 15:3-4; I Corinthians 15:55-57; Mark 16:1-8; Matthew 28:1-9

hymn.title: Come, ye faithful, raise the strain
O sons and daughters, let us sing
"Welcome, happy morning!" age to age shall say
The day of resurrection
Thine is the glory
Hail, Thou once despised Jesus
The Head that once was crowned with thorns
The Lord ascendeth up on high
Crown Him with many crowns
O Holy Saviour, Friend unseen
Jesus, Thou Joy of loving hearts
Jesus, Lover of my soul
O Son of Man, our Hero strong and tender
Since Jesus is my Friend
O Thou, in all Thy might so far
I've found a Friend, O such a Friend
Thou art the Way: to Thee alone
Jesus, stand among us
Jesus merciful
I know not how that Bethlehem's Babe
Jesus, kneel beside me
Blest are the pure in heart
We bear the strain of earthly care
Strong son of God, immortal Love
Immortal Love, forever full
The Lord will come and not be slow
Rejoice, rejoice, believers
The King shall come when morning dawns
hymn.scripture: II Peter 1:19; Matthew 25:31; Song of Solomon 6:10

hymn.title: Come, Lord, and tarry not
Lo He comes, with clouds descending
Breathe on me, Breath of God
Spirit of God, descend upon my heart
Come, Holy Ghost, our souls inspire
Seal us, O Holy Spirit
Come, Holy Spirit, heavenly Dove
Holy Spirit, Truth divine
Gracious spirit, dwell with me
O spirit of the living God
Spirit divine, attend our prayers
Come; Thou Almighty King
O Trinity of blessed light
Ancient of Days, who sittest throned in glory
O God of Light, The Word, a lamp unfailing
Book of books, our people's strength
Father of mercies, in Thy Word
Break Thou the bread of life
O Word of God Incarnate
Lord, Thy word abideth
How I love Thy law, O Lord
Lamp of our feet, whereby we trace
O come, my people, to my law
O Lord, of life, to Thee we lift
Most perfect is the law of God
How shall the young direct their way
The heavens declare Thy glory, Lord
The Spirit breathes upon the Word
Come to the Saviour now
Thy life was given for me
Hark, my soul, it is the Lord
Art thou weary, art thou languid
Sing them over again to me
O Jesus, Thou art standard
Jesus is tenderly calling thee home
"Come unto Me, ye weary"
Jesus calls us: o'er the tumult
Lord Jesus, think on me
Rock of Ages, cleft for me
Just as I am, without one plea
Depth of mercy! can there be
Because I knew not when my life was good
Amazing grace, how sweet the sound
There is a fountain filled with blood
Lord, from the depths to Thee I cried
I am coming to the cross
Jesus, I my cross have taken
I heard the voice of Jesus say
How blest is he whose trespass
God be merciful to me
Go, labor on: spend, and be spent
Draw Thou my soul, O Christ
Father, we greet Thee, God of Love, whose glory
I bind my heart this tide
Come, labor on
Lord God of Hosts, whose purpose, never swerving
So let our lips and lives express
Must Jesus bear the cross alone
Hope of the world, Thou Christ of great compassion
I'm not ashamed to own my Lord
"Take up thy cross," the Saviour said
We thank Thee, Lord, Thy paths of service lead
Christ of the Upward Way
Come, ye that fear the Lord, and hear
work, for the night is coming
Lord, speak to me, that I may speak
Master, no offering
Take time to be holy
A charge to keep I have
Have Thine own way, Lord
Be Thou my vision, O Lord of my heart
O Master, let me walk with Thee
O Thou who makest souls to shine
Take Thou our minds, dear Lord, we humbly pray
O Jesus, I have promised
Make me a captive, Lord
Father, whose will is life and good
Take my life, and let it be
Saviour! Thy dying love
We give Thee but Thine own
All things are Thine; no gift have we
Christ, of all my hopes the Ground
From Thee all skill and science flow
More about Jesus would I know
Lord, I want to be a Christian
There is a place of quiet rest
O for a closer walk with God
I am Thine, O Lord
My spirit longs for Thee
As pants the hart for cooling streams
O let my supplicating cry
I need Thee every hour
O for a heart to praise my God
Nearer, my God, to Thee
O Lord, my God, most earnestly
Father of peace, and God of love
O God, regard my humble plea
Rise, my soul, and stretch thy wings
Saviour, like a shepherd lead us
Lead, kindly Light, amid the encircling gloom
Lead on, O King Eternal
O brothers, lift your voices
Jesus, lead the way
hymn.scripture: Hebrews 12:2; II Corinthians 4:17; II Timothy 2:12; Matthew 6:34

hymn.title: Jesus, Saviour, pilot me
Far off I see the goal
He leadeth me: O blessed thought
Guide me, O Thou great Jehovah
Children of the Heavenly King
Lead us, O Father, in the paths of peace
O God of Bethel, by whose hand
Lead us, Heavenly Father, lead us
If thou but suffer God to guide thee
He who would valiant be
Awake, my soul, stretch every nerve
God is my strong Salvation
Faith of our fathers! living still
Stand up, stand up for Jesus
Onward, Christian soldiers
March on, o soul, with strength
Rise up, O men of God
Am I a soldier of the cross
hymn.scripture: II Timothy 2:1; II Timothy 2:12; II Timothy 2:3

hymn.title: The Son of God goes forth to war
O grant us light, that we may know
Who is on the Lord's side
We are living, we are dwelling
Now Israel may say, and that in truth
God of grace and God of glory
Fight the good fight with all thy might
Christian, dost thou see them
Once to every man and nation
Soldiers of Christ, arise
My soul, be on thy guard
Give to the winds thy fears
All the way my Saviour leads me
Whate're my God ordains is right
My Jesus, as Thou wilt
My hope is built on nothing less
How firm a foundation, ye saints of the Lord
I love the Lord, His strength is mine
Ask ye what great thing I know
Grace and truth shall mark the way
Come, ye disconsolate, where're ye languish
Be still, my soul: the Lord is on thy side
Who trusts in God, a strong abode
Jesus; keep me near the cross
I to the hills will lift my eyes
My faith looks up to Thee
Come, Thou Fount of every blessing
God is our Refuge and our Strength
Not so in haste my heart
I love to tell the story
Father, in Thy mysterious presence kneeling
What a Friend we have in Jesus
Approach, my soul, the mercy seat
To God my earnest voice I raise
O Lord Most High, with all my heart
Where high the heavenly temple stands
Open my eyes, that I may see
Prayer is the soul's sincere desire
O Lord, make haste to hear my cry
Thy loving-kindness, Lord, is good and free
In the hour of trial
God be in my head
O gracious God forsake me not
More love to Thee, O Christ
Sweet hour of prayer, sweet hour of Prayer
Love divine, all loves excelling
O Love that wilt not let me go
Jesus, the very thought of Thee
I sought the Lord, and afterward I knew
Tell me the old, old story
Jesus, Thy boundless love to me
My Jesus, I love Thee
My heart is resting, O my God
Rejoice, ye pure in heart
Come, we that love the Lord
My God, I thank Thee, who hast made
The King of Glory standeth
Take the name of Jesus with you
The Lord I will at all times bless
I waited for the Lord my God
Jesus, priceless treasure
O Morning Star, how fair and bright
Dear Lord and Father of mankind
In heavenly love abiding
Sometimes a light surprises
From every stormy wind that blows
Peace, perfect peace, in this dark world of sin
They cast their nets in Galilee
The steps of those whom He approves
Thou hidden Source of calm repose
O what their joy and their glory must be
For all the saints who from their labors rest
Hark! hark, my soul! angelic songs are swelling
Ten thousand times ten thousand
Jerusalem the golden
For thee, O dear, dear country
Brief life is here our portion
O where are kings and empires now
Built on the Rock the Church doth stand
Christ is made the sure Foundation
Glorious things of thee are spoken
I love Thy Kingdom, Lord
City of God, how broad and far
hymn.scripture: Isaiah 26:1; Matthew 6:10; Matthew 6:33; Psalms 48:12; Psalms 48:2; Psalms 48:8

hymn.title: The Church's one Foundation
Within Thy temple's sacred courts
With joy I heard my friends exclaim
How dear to me, O Lord of Hosts
Pleasant are Thy courts above
Here, O my Lord,I see Thee face to face
A parting hymn we sing
According to Thy gracious word 444
Bread of the world in mercy broken
Be known to us in breaking bread
Let us break bread together
'Twas on that night when doomed to know
For the bread, which Thou hast broken
O Bread of Life, for all men broken
Jesus, Friend, so kind and gentle
O Jesus Christ, our Lord most dear
O perfect Love, all human thought transcending
O Love divine and golden
O happy home, where Thou art loved the dearest
All things bright and beautiful
Saviour, teach me, day by day
Father, lead me day by day
Tell me the stories of Jesus
I think when I read that sweet story of old
It fell upon a summer day
Once in royal David's city
With happy voices ringing
Morning has broken
Jesus loves me this I know
God who made the earth
Father, we thank Thee for the night
O Thou whose feet have climbed life's hill
Now in the days of youth
We would be building; temples still undone
Shepherd of eager youth
Just as I am, Thine own to be
Blest be the tie that binds
O brother man, fold to thy heart thy brother
Through the night of doubt and sorrow
Forgive, O Lord, our severing ways
Put forth, o God,Thy Spirit's might
Hills of the North, rejoice
In Christ there is no East or West
Let there be light, Lord God of Hosts
Lift up our hearts, O King of Kings
The light of God is falling
O God of love, O King of peace
"Thy Kingdom come," on bended knee
Eternal God, whose power upholds
Father eternal, Ruler of creation
God the omnipotent! King, who ordainest
Thy Kingdom come, O Lord
Christ for the world we sing
Turn back, o man, forswear thy foolish ways
O Zion, haste, thy mission high fulfilling
Christ is the world's true Light
Lord, bless and pity us
Ye Christian heralds, go proclaim
Remember all the people
Jesus shall reign where're the sun
Arm of the Lord, awake, awake
Heralds of Christ, who bear the King's commands
The morning light is breaking
God is working, His purpose out
The ends of all the earth shall hear
Christ shall have dominion
We have heard the joyful sound
We've a story to tell to the nations
Hail to the brightness of Zion's glad morning
Fling out the banner! let it float
Where cross the crowded ways of life
O Holy City, seen of John
From ocean unto ocean
O beautiful for spacious skies
O God of earth and alter
Not alone for mighty empire
My country, 'tis of thee
God bless our native land
God of our fathers, whose almighty hand
My song forever shall record
Judge eternal, throned in splendor
Arise, o Lord, our God, arise
We dedicate this temple
Good of the prophets! Bless the prophets' sons
Eternal Father, strong to save
Almighty Father, strong to save
O God, beneath, Thy guiding hand
We plow the fields, and scatter
Come, ye thankful people, come
Ring out the old, ring in the new
Great God, we sing that mighty hand
Let all who enter here
Come, my soul, thy suit prepare
Father, the watches of the night are o'er
Come, dearest Lord, descend and dwell
O Thou who hearest every heartfelt prayer
Bless Thou the gifts our hands have brought
Lord, for the mercies of the night
Let the words of my mouth
Hear our prayer, O Lord
To my humble supplication
Create in me a clean heart, O God
Father, fill us with Thy love
Lead me, Lord, lead me in Thy righteousness
The lone, wild fowl in lofty flight
Day by day
Almighty Father, hear our prayer
Part in peace: Christ's life was peace
Praise God from whom all blessings flow
